    "summary": "A passionate and experienced DUO-certified (1e graads bevoegd)\u202fEnglish instructor, born to be a teacher, with seventeen years of continuous teaching experience in middle schools, high schools, universities, and language institutes; seven years of engagement in teacher training programs and seven years of educational leadership experience. Knowledgeable of modern teaching methods and international curricula (Task-Based Language Teaching (TBLT), Content and Language Integrated Learning (CLIL), Design-Based Education (DBE), International Baccalaureate (IB), Middle Years Programme (MYP), etc), materials development, and assessment systems. Currently a teacher trainer at NHL Stenden University of Applied Sciences (international teacher education), an English instructor (English for Specific Purposes (ESP) and English for Academic Purposes (EAP)) at the University of Groningen, and the Coordinator at the English Academy for Newcomers (EAN), Groningen. Committed to fostering a creative, innovative, and inclusive environment for English language development by maintaining motivation and enhancing enthusiasm in language learners; employing coaching skills to improve students\u2019 achievements; passionate about educational leadership engagement.",
